		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Like other people said, these video artifacts are completely normal, and it's the reason why composite video sucks.<br /><br />If you care about getting decent video quality out of an NES, I'd recommend looking into viletim's NESRGB boards:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://etim.net.au/nesrgb/">https://etim.net.au/nesrgb/</a><!-- m --><br />The mod requires quite a bit of soldering (and desoldering!) skills, but if you aren't familiar with it, maybe you can get someone to help you.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
