		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: NES video - is this normal??</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Odyssey2 uses Intel 8244/8245, whose video generation methodology I haven't been able to determine.<br /></div>The 8244/8245 emits RGBI video.<br /><br />A separate IC (&quot;612160-1&quot;) is fed <a href="https://console5.com/wiki/File:Odyssey2-Schematic.png" class="postlink">3.579545MHz, and a 105°(??) delayed copy via an R-L-C.</a><br /><br />Without any particularly good evidence, I'd guess the NTSC encoder is running a digital multiplexer fed by these two phases, effectively rotating between just three of the RGB inputs, and then that composite signal is combined with the Intensity, Composite Sync, and blanking inputs to generate the desired composite signal.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


